      "review_summary": "The PR adds `needs_stdin_isolation` to conditionally redirect installer subprocess stdin in `scripts/install.sh` and adds regression tests for piped and direct stdin behavior.\n\nPR surface: Tests +191, Other +34. Total +225 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: current docs advertise `curl | bash`, current main lets gum-wrapped and fallback subprocesses inherit stdin, and gum v0.17.0 forwards `os.Stdin` to the wrapped command. I did not run a live current-main WSL2 installer repro in this read-only review.",
